China Resources Enterprise (SEHK: 291) is the subsidiary and the listed company of China Resources Holdings. It is a conglomerate enterprise focusing on retailing, beverage, food processing and distribution, textiles and real estate in Hong Kong and Mainland China. Its assets include a 51% share in CR Snow, the largest brewing company in China and a joint venture with SAB Miller.
It is a Hang Seng Index Constituent Stock (blue chip) and Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index Constitute Stock (red chip) in the Hong Kong stock market.
